"content": "<p>A case for carrying arrows on hunting expeditions or in battle.</p>\n<h2>Quivers used on hunting expeditions</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:3\">GEN 27:3</a></p>\n<h2>Loaded quivers taken into battle</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job39:23\">JOB 39:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:6\">ISA 22:6</a></p>\n<h2>Quivers referred to figuratively</h2>\n<h3>To depict the deadly fire-power of an enemy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:16\">JER 5:16</a></p>\n<h3>As a symbol of a man's many sons</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps127:5\">PSA 127:5</a></p>\n<h3>To depict the LORD's concealment of his servant</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:2\">ISA 49:2</a></p>\n<h3>As an instrument of the LORD's discipline</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:13\">LAM 3:13</a></p>",
